body:
`line_multi` layout is broken because it receives `NaN` as width. 
This PR fixes the issue. 

@williaster @graceguo-supercat @michellethomas @conglei

Use native html instead. 
This is part of gradually moving away from reactable. 

@michellethomas @graceguo-supercat @williaster @conglei

- Down version `reactable` to `1.0.2` due to issue with production #5935.
- Remove `fastdom` which is listed as dependency but never used.

@michellethomas @graceguo-supercat @williaster @conglei

default is `1000x600` which is kinda small and sometimes cause overflow on the right side. 
changing to `1280x800`

@michellethomas @graceguo-supercat @williaster @conglei

- Move `countries` geojson files directory under `CountryMap`. 
- To make it clearer that these geojson are only for the `CountryMap`

@graceguo-supercat @michellethomas @williaster @conglei

This PR removes future imports from the rest of the files that are not migrations or tests. 
This PR also updates the contributing.md instructions. 

@john-bodley @mistercrunch

This PR will add back changes of #5991 that were reverted by #6035. This PR will close #5821

The travis configuration changes resolved the postgres test stuck issue

@graceguo-supercat  We can attach details of travis change as well for future reference.

Since we now no longer support python2, This PR starts taking out the __future__ imports from tests and utils. 
I will follow up with the same thing for other parts of the code base and also do the same for six and utf8. 

@john-bodley @mistercrunch
